rComments: Great prof! He doesn't record his lectures so make sure you show up. He did have a few technical challenges with Zoom but nothing major. He listens to students and would ask for our feedback about the midterms and exam. As long as you stay on top of lectures and readings (which I didn't do at first - that's on me), you'll do great.

Not my cup of tea, but wasn't bad. I hated the group project, but it might have just been my group because they were very lazy... pretty boring lectures, but did learn some things. He does care for his students though, I'm just not a fan of his lecture/class style. Also easy to follow if you are in immersion!

Prof. Chelbi - some people don't mind him, some really don't like him. If you're taking this course online, it should be super easy to pass because the exams are based on the powerpoints. He can sometimes come across as rude when he responds to student questions because he's blunt. But, he is very helpful and is always free to email.

Kind of prof that will tell you that what matters is that you understand the concepts, and then shoots you a question like: what's the name of the school? Prof repeats himself for an hour and a half, hard to follow, boring, frustrating. Kind of prof that a 4th grader student could easily remplace. He recycles his different courses and sounds simila

Great teacher. I've had him in a couple of CMN classes. He is very caring and understanding. His tests are easy, no surprises. Tells you what you will be graded on. He is a very easy grader on papers. Always gives the student the benefit of the doubt. Would absolutely recommend him to anyone.

Ce n'est pas la première classe que je suis avec ce professeur, mais j'espère que ce sera la dernière. Athmane est attachant, il fait tout pour nous divertir. Mais il a un effet assez soporifique, et se montre injoignable en dehors des classes, particulièrement en cette période compliquée. Examens sous forme de QCM ici, et pas de lecture à faire.
He cares about the students learning. loved this class. Listen and read the chapters he asks and you will get an A with ease.
Professor Chelbi is a knowledgeable, down-to-earth teacher who has great passion for what he teaches. He is so well versed in all the subjects he teaches. I HANDS DOWN recommend him to anyone!
He is a very outgoing prof and loves to connect with his students. As a teacher he knows what he is talking about. Always super positive and a very fair marker on groups projects.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Professor Chelbi was super funny. Unfortunately, i will not be taking any of his classes again. His grading criteria for our group project was not clear and even though we asked him many questions about it, his answers were very vague. Not enough explanations when it came to the group project.

He's a very good professor! U will learn a lot.. Very clear in his explanations and very relax in class. As long as you do all your work you will pass. Always asked if we understood the material or if we had any questions. The group projects were actually fun and easy.

Doesn't base his midterms on the textbook but he says it helps for better understanding. Good humoured & friendly (call him batman lol). He enjoys interactions with his students & will to crack jokes from time to time :) would recommend.
Wonderful, brilliant person and very approachable! Attend class. You'll learn a lot. He really cares for his students. Explanations are very clear. Will definitely take another class with him again.
The best professor I have ever had. He's very funny and entertaining during lectures. Love the accent!
I loved this class. Athmane teaches it really well; he's incredibly smart. Knows what he's talking about. A lot of my friends love him.
Prof goes off talking about random things, grades take forever to get back (only recieved one midterm back before the final), not a horrible proff just not organized.

Easy to follow and so very sweet and super helpful! Will help you with anything and doesn't mind staying after class to help you with whatever you need. Wants everyone to do well, a very interesting class... I learned so much and had a lot of fun.
